BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Material and Light: A Conversation with Artist Nancy Lorenz
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260328T150000
UID:10001957-1774706400-1774710000@www.taubmanmuseum.org
DESCRIPTION:Nancy Lorenz: The Elements Nancy Lorenz\, Moonlight\, 2023\, s
 ilver leaf\, mother of pearl\, shellac\, pigment on wood panel\, 36 x 60 i
 n.\, courtesy of the artist Get an extra special sneak peek at an upcoming
  exhibition with artist Nancy Lorenz in advance of her solo exhibition\, T
 he Elements\, opening February 2027 here at the Taubman Museum of Art. In 
 conversation with Curator Laura K. Higgins\, Lorenz will explore her disti
 nctive practice\, which draws on a lifetime of engagement with rich materi
 als and surface techniques. Lorenz’s luminous works—layered with gold\
 , silver\, and palladium leaf\, mother-of-pearl inlay\, resin\, and lacque
 r—reflect both Western abstraction and deep influence from traditional J
 apanese craft and aesthetics\, a sensibility first seeded during her forma
 tive years in Tokyo. Presented in dialogue with selections of Japanese pri
 nts and a kimono from the Museum’s Sharing Collection\, this program sit
 uates Lorenz’s material language within broader artistic and cultural li
 neages\, offering insight into the ideas and influences that will shape he
 r forthcoming exhibition. Members Free | General Public: $8 Not a Member? 
 Join today and receive benefits such as discounts on classes and camps\, i
 nvitations to exclusive events\, free reciprocal membership to the Virgini
 a Museum of Fine Arts in Richmond\, and more! Click here to learn more. Ad
 d to Calendar Driving? Get Directions Share This! Register Now Date: Feb 0
 4\, 2027 May 16\, 2027\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/conversati
 on-with-nancy-lorenz
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/conversation-with-nancy-lorenz
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Architectural Highlights Behind-the-Scenes Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T193000
UID:10001942-1775239200-1775244600@www.taubmanmuseum.org
DESCRIPTION:Nancy Lorenz: The Elements Discover the Taubman Museum of Art 
 from a whole new perspective during this Architectural Highlights Tour\, a
 n engaging\, behind-the-scenes experience that reveals the vision\, innova
 tion\, and craftsmanship behind one of Roanoke’s most iconic landmarks t
 hat Architectural Digest named one of the best designed museums in the nat
 ion. Led in collaboration with local architects and individuals directly i
 nvolved in the creation of the building\, this approximately 90-minute gui
 ded tour traces the Museum’s architectural story from the ground up. Des
 igned by Randall Stout and inspired by the natural forms of Virginia’s l
 andscape\, the building’s soaring glass\, steel\, patinated zinc\, and l
 ocally sourced Hokie Stone come alive through expert insight and little-kn
 own details. Along the way\, guests will explore dramatic interior spaces\
 , flexible performance and gallery areas\, the “Vault” where artworks 
 not on view are stored\, and the sophisticated systems that protect the Mu
 seum’s art while welcoming the community. The tour culminates at the Top
  of the Taubman Balcony\, where sweeping views of downtown Roanoke\, the r
 ailroad corridor\, and surrounding landmarks provide a fitting finale. Gue
 sts are invited to raise a glass during a celebratory champagne toast to c
 ap off this special experience. Whether you’re a design enthusiast\, arc
 hitecture professional\, or curious local\, this special tour offers rare 
 access\, compelling stories\, and a memorable way to experience the Taubma
 n Museum of Art. Add to Calendar Driving? Get Directions Share This! Regis
 ter Now Date: Feb 04\, 2027 May 16\, 2027\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmu
 seum.org/arch-tour-april-3
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/arch-tour-april-3
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
